  "text": "The regulation of morphogenesis in various organs such as lung, kidney, skin and limbs [CITATION_1] Davies et al., 1995, Kulyk and [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] is the result of complex processes in which the regulation of the extracellular matrix (ECM) plays a key role. The control of ECM composition has therefore to be considered as a main aspect for both cell strategy and the influence of environmental factors on cellular behavior.",
